{"name": "pytest-porcochu", "metadata": {"name": "pytest-porcochu", "version": "1.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Framework :: Pytest", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Software Development :: Testing"], "home_page": "https://github.com/saet/pytest-porcochu", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Show surprise when tests are passing", "upload_time": 1732814099}, "documentation": ["# pytest-porcochu\n\nLike `pytest-pikachu` but it's a pikachuified pig.\n\n`pytest-porcochu` prints ascii art of Surprised Porco when all tests pass.\n\n## Installation\n\n```\n$ pip install pytest-porcochu\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nPass the `--porcochu` option to `pytest` as a command line flag or configuration\nfile option to get these stunning effects.\n\n```\n$ pytest --porcochu\n============================= test session starts ==============================\nplatform linux -- Python 3.9.6, pytest-6.2.4, py-1.10.0, pluggy-0.13.1\nrootdir: /home/.../pytest-porcochu, configfile: tox.ini, testpaths: tests\nplugins: porcochu-0.1.0\ncollected 4 items\n\ntests/test_plugin.py ....                                                [100%]\n\n============================== 4 passed in 0.11s ===============================\n\n%%%%@%%%%%%%%%@%%%%%%%#########%%%#%%######################%@%%##*+===---=-::::\n%%%%@%%%@%%%%%@%%%%########################################%@%###*+==-::-=-.:::\n@@%@@%%%@@%%%%@@%%%######%##########%################*###**#@%*=--==--::--:::-:\n%%@%%%%%@%#----::::-=**#####%%%%%#%%##################*+:----==---==---:--:..::\n%%@%%%%%%%%=--=========-:+##%%%############*#######+:--=======---+=---::-:. .::\n%@@%%%%%%%%%=---==========:.+#%%###############*=:.:-=======----=+=---::-:. .::\n%@@%%%%%%%%%*------==+++++=:...-=+=:.    .:--:...::-======--::::+==---::-:. .::\n%%%%%%%%%%%%%-:::::--==+++==-.                  .::-===----:-::-+=---:::--:..::\n@@%@%%%%@@@@%*-:-::--==+==++-.                   .-===----:::::++==---::--:.:-:\n@@@@@@@@@@@@%%+--:::---===+=:..                  .-=--=-:::::-+++===--===++=+**\n@@@@@@@@@@@@%@%*--:::::--:--::::...           ....::::::::::=#%#%%####%%%%%%%%%\n@@@@@@@@@@@@+==+%+----:::::--::-=::...       ..#::--:::::-=*%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%\n@@@@@@@@@%-:===#%%%*=--::-=:-.:-:::.....     .:...-#*---*#@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@\n------=+=::-==+#%@@%%#++++:--.:::....:..       ...:-@%##%@@@@@@@@@@@@#*%@@@@@@@\n-:::-==---=+===#@%%%%%%%#:--:.:::....:...   .   ...:=%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%#%%%%%%%%\n:::::---===++==#@@@@@%%%:---::::.....:..::::.  ....::%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%\n:::::--:-=++==+%@@@@@@%%:--::::::::.:.:--:::-:...:.::##%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%\n::::--:-+*+#*+#%%@@@@@@--::::::::::::=+#----#+-:.:.::-###%%%%%%%%%%%%@%@@@%%%%%\n-:::---=*%*%@@%%@@@@@@%--:::::::-:--=-:-====-:::::::::%%%###%%%%%%%%%##%%%@@@@%\n=-::--=++**%@@@@@@@@@@*--::::--------==+++++==-:::::::#@%@@%%%%#***********##%#\n:-::--=+++*%@@@@@@@@@@*-----::--------=+====---:::::::=@@@@@%%#****************\n::-:::==+*#@@@@@@@@@@@=---------=====----------::--::::%@@@@%******************\n---:---=+*%@@@@@@@@@@@#----=+========+========++=--:::-+@@@%#******#***********\n----:--=+*%@@@@@@@@@@@@---:-=*#+++==+====++*#*=-:::::---%@@%#*******#**********\n==--+++++*#@@@@@@@@@@@@#--::--+##*+++=++****+=-:::::-=--=@@##******#***********\n#++++==++**%@@%%%%@@@@@=--::::-+*##********==-:::::--==--#@%#**++**************\n===+++****+==-------:---=--::::-***+******+=---::::=+++++==+==========+********\n++++****+++++====++=++====-:::::+*+++=++++=-----:-+++==+==-----=-------====----\n\n```\n\n## Prior art\n\nI wrote this `pytest` plugin after seeing [this Reddit thread][1]. I used the\nanswer in [this Stack Overflow question][2] on how to pass information between\ndifferent `pytest` hooks.\n\n## License\n\nDistributed under the terms of the MIT license, `pytest-porcochu` is free and\nopen source software.\n\n[1]:\n  https://www.reddit.com/r/ProgrammerHumor/comments/a381ur/the_correct_reaction_to_unit_tests_passing/\n[2]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/53640991\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pytest_porcochu", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "pytest_porcochu.plugin", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pytest_porcochu.plugin.pytest_sessionfinish", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "session", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exitstatus", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Attach the exit status to the session config so we can read it later.\n\nWe need this in order to tell whether the test run passed or not."]}, {"name": "pytest_porcochu.plugin.pytest_unconfigure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Show the surprised porcochu if enabled when all tests pass."]}, {"name": "pytest_porcochu.plugin.pytest_addoption", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parser", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add a CLI flag to enable showing surprise."]}], "variables": [{"name": "pytest_porcochu.plugin.ascii_art", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}